          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p>Reaction at C2 is disfavored because the aromaticity of the benzene ring is lost.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbFFhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--f5e0aa7a1bd7b65eab667a351c0eaadae554710a/OChem_24_EC_207.jpg\" alt=\"Structure of indole with arrows showing C 3 attacking electrophile. Resulting resonance structures show loss of aromaticity due to 8 electrons in pi system.\">"
